The www.example.com domain has a cross-site scripting vulnerability of the reflected type.

**Vulnerable script:** https://example.com/index.php
**Vulnerable parameter:** GET param
**Exploitation conditions:** any external intruder
**Testing environment:** Firefox Quantum 65.0 (64-bit), Burp Suite Community Edition v1.7.36
**Example of exploitation:**
1. Go to the URL https://example.com/index.php
2. As a payload in the GET parameter *param* we use the string `”> <svg / onload = alert ()>`.

